# Public repo hygiene (Rule34-Browser)

Repo: https://github.com/justAleks0/Rule34-Browser (public). Treat every change as potentially publishable.

## Before finishing a task

### 1. Secrets & `.gitignore`

Never commit credentials or local config. These must stay gitignored:

- `firebase-config.json`, `firebase-session.dat`, API keys, `.env`, keystores (`.pfx`, `.jks`), `google-services.json`
- `dist/`, `bin/`, `obj/`, `*.apk`, build artifacts

If a new secret path or generated output appears, **add it to `.gitignore` at repo root** in the same turn. Android native project (`R34Browser`) has its own repo — apply the same rules there when editing it.

### 2. Version numbers (app changes only)

When behavior or user-visible UI changes (see `version-bump-always.mdc`):

| Platform | File | Field |
|----------|------|--------|
| Desktop | `Rule34GalleryApp/Rule34GalleryApp.csproj` | `<Version>x.y.z</Version>` |
| Android | `R34Browser/app/build.gradle.kts` | `versionName` + increment `versionCode` |
| README | `README.md` | **Current version** line at top |

Same semver on both platforms. Docs-only / `.cursor/` rules-only → skip bump unless user asks.

### 3. Changelog (one format everywhere)

Use the **same structure** in:

- `changelog.md` (repo root — bundled in desktop + Android via version badge)
- GitHub Releases (extracted from `changelog.md` by `scripts/publish-github-release.ps1`)
- Any new version entry from the bump hook (`scripts/changelog-format.ps1`)

Canonical copy: **`changelog-template.md`**

```markdown
# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented here.

---

## [Version Number] - HH-mm MM-DD-YYYY

### Added
- New features, new files, new systems, new options.

### Changed
- Things that already existed but were adjusted, improved, renamed, reworked, or redesigned.

### Fixed
- Bugs, broken behavior, crashes, wrong text, missing files, weird issues.

### Removed
- Deleted features, removed files, removed old systems, abandoned options.

### Notes
- Extra context, warnings, known issues, setup info, or things users should know.

---
```

**Rules:**
- Version line uses **24-hour** `HH-mm MM-DD-YYYY` (example: `## 2.0.84 - 14-30 07-02-2026`)
- Put each bullet under the right `###` heading; **omit** empty sections (no "None" placeholders)
- Name the surface in bullets when helpful: `(PC)`, `(Android)`, `(PC + Android)`
- End each version block with `---` before the next version

**Do not:** `Auto version bump`, `Maintenance release`, `Release vX`, or bullets that only say the version changed.

After editing `changelog.md`, run `scripts/sync-changelog-android.ps1`.

### 4. README (`README.md`)

Update when features, platforms, or major behavior change. README describes **what the project is**, not how to clone/build/install.

**Include:** product summary, client roles table, feature areas, releases link, config note (secrets local/gitignored), changelog pointer.

**Exclude from README:** step-by-step `git clone`, `dotnet build`, install scripts, architecture deep-dives, mermaid diagrams — keep those in scripts, wiki, or separate docs if needed.

When shipping something new, add or extend a bullet under the right **Features** subsection and bump **Current version** at the top.

### 5. GitHub Releases (`scripts/publish-github-release.ps1`)

Release notes **must** be copied from the matching `changelog.md` version block (including `### Added` / `### Changed` / etc.).

**Do:**
- Write the version block in `changelog.md` first (template in `changelog-template.md`)
- Run `scripts/publish-github-release.ps1` (or `-SkipBuild` after `post-change-all.ps1`)
- Confirm on GitHub that the release body shows the `###` sections, not `Release vX`

**Do not:** Publish generic one-line release text.

**Fix notes on an existing release:**
```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/publish-github-release.ps1 -EditOnly -Tag v2.0.83
```

### 6. Final message checklist

If app code changed, include the post-change block from `publish-and-install-after-edits.mdc`.

If only docs/rules changed, say so and skip publish/install.
